The dome of provision and reward of Mawlid

Grand-Shaykh `Abdullah al-Fa'iz ad-Daghestani said, “The one who made Mawlid an-Nabi and the Angel of Death took his soul after a long life, if he observed Mawlid an-Nabi only one time, from half of the strong huge angels that have been given to Prophet ﷺ that have descended on his invitation (to Mawlid) will go with him to the grave ascending all the way to heavens, seeking Allah’s forgiveness for him, from the time of the Mawlid he attended, to his grave and to Judgment Day.” 
 
That is why Prophet ﷺ said, Iqraa YaSeen `ala mawtaakum, “Recite Surah YaSeen on your dead.” Surah YaSeen is the heart of the Qur`an. When you read it, you are honoring Sayyidina Muhammad (s) and all these angels will be with you. Half of them you take with you. 

As Imam al-Busayri said, “If we observe Mawlid every day it is not enough.” Do it every day, you get half of those angels. Do it one time you got those angels; do it another time you get them again and each time it is different angels, not the same ones. Do Mawlid and Allah (swt) will send half of them to your grave reciting Allah's Praise and all will be written for you. And when someone dies where do they go? Half of them go with his heirs. Not inheritance from somewhere else, outside the family, but half of these angels will be for his heirs, from his blood; that is the reward for that person celebrating the Prophet's birthday. 

Mawlana Shaykh Hisham 
Kabbani🌸
